					<head>Derashot</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of short discourses and notes on various passages of Scripture and other subjects, mostly (or entirely) by Mordekhai Dato (partly his autograph).</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="ita">Hebrew, Italian</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85085046">
							<locus from="1r" to="70v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Derashot </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">דרשות</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/53080919">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/53080919" xml:lang="en">Dato, Mordecai ben Judah, 1525-</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/53080919" xml:lang="he">דאטו, מרדכי </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Among the contents are: commentaries on the Prophets, the prophecies of Yo'el ben Uzi'el, a list of expenses incurred on a journey to Ferrara, short discourses in Italian, a fragmentary sketch of Mafteaḥ ha-Zohar, a homily on marriage in Italian and Hebrew, commentaries on the prophecy, sacrifices, providence, prayer, etc. </p>
							</note>
							<filiation>Cf, Add MS 27008 for a similar collection of commentaries by the same author.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the latter part of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex.</support>
								<extent>70 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>140/205</height>
										<width>105/145</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>70 folios (+ 3 paper flyleaves at the beginning and 1 older and 3 modern paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Original quiring not established due to a modern restoration (leaves on guards).</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several folios slightly mutilated.</p>
									<p>Slightly stained.</p>
									<p>Fading ink.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="15 50" writtenLines="15 50">
									<p>Nearly no side margins left by the scribe.</p>
									<p>Many marginal notes and additions.</p>
									<p>Scribal erasures (e.g. folio 31v, 32r).</p>
									<p>Catchowords on some of the versos, mostly cut away.</p>
									<p>Various layouts and handwritings.</p>
									<p>Folios 64-70 arranged in two columns, with visible pencil ruling, mostly left unfilled. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
